ACC Data Tracer

Author : Yacine Ould Rouis - Barcelona Supercomputing Center (BSC) - yacine.ouldrouis@bsc.es

Small tool to trace OpenACC GPU data allocations using NV_ACC_NOTIFY and
visualize them as a timeline.

The tool records GPU allocation events, timestamps them, adds the MPI rank
when available, and generates a JSON report that can be visualized in a browser.

Files

acc-data-trace.py
    Wrapper that instruments and runs a command line, and parses execution logs into a json report (using acc_pipeline_prepare.py).

acc_pipeline_prepare.py (internal)
    Parses the raw trace log and produces a JSON report describing GPU
    allocation lifetimes.

acc-data-view.html
    Browser interface to visualize the GPU memory timeline.


Usage

Run the tracer before your normal command. Everything after "--" is executed
exactly as you would normally run it.

Examples

MPI using mpirun:

    ./acc-data-trace.py -out report.json -- mpirun -np 4 --bind-to none ./alya cavnas

MPI using srun (Slurm):

    ./acc-data-trace.py -out report.json -- srun -n 4 ./alya cavnas

Serial execution:

    ./acc-data-trace.py -out report.json -- ./unitt_adr_3d_openacc


What the wrapper does

- sets NV_ACC_NOTIFY=18
- timestamps every output line
- detects MPI ranks when possible
- writes an execution log
- runs acc_pipeline_prepare.py to parse the log and generate the JSON report


Output

log file (default: out)

    execution logs + timestamps and ranks for each line

    Example:
        [0.123456][rank=0] create CUDA data ...
        [0.123789][rank=1] alloc CUDA data ...

JSON report (default: report.json)

    Processed allocation timeline used by the viewer.


Visualization

Open the viewer in a browser:

    acc-data-view.html

Load the generated JSON file to display the GPU allocation timeline.
